{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 06 — Maximum Likelihood Estimation\n",
    "**References:** Casella & Berger (2002) Ch. 7 · Lehmann & Casella (1998) Ch. 6 · Wasserman (2004) Ch. 9\n",
    "\n",
    "## Narrative thread\n",
    "```\n",
    "Likelihood function -> Score -> MLE -> Consistency -> Asymptotic normality -> Efficiency -> Observed information\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. The likelihood function\n",
    "\n",
    "Given data $\\mathbf{x} = (x_1,\\ldots,x_n)$ and model $f(\\mathbf{x}\\mid\\theta)$, the **likelihood** is:\n",
    "$$L(\\theta \\mid \\mathbf{x}) = f(\\mathbf{x} \\mid \\theta) = \\prod_{i=1}^n f(x_i \\mid \\theta)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The **log-likelihood** is $\\ell(\\theta) = \\log L(\\theta) = \\sum_{i=1}^n \\log f(x_i \\mid \\theta)$.\n",
    "\n",
    "The **MLE** is $\\hat{\\theta} = \\arg\\max_\\theta L(\\theta) = \\arg\\max_\\theta \\ell(\\theta)$.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Score equation:** At a regular interior maximum:\n",
    "$$\\frac{\\partial \\ell}{\\partial \\theta}\\bigg|_{\\theta=\\hat\\theta} = 0$$\n",
    "\n",
    "> The likelihood is a function of $\\theta$ (not a probability density in $\\theta$). It measures how well each $\\theta$ value explains the observed data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from scipy import stats, optimize\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({\n",
    "    'figure.dpi': 130, 'axes.spines.top': False, 'axes.spines.right': False,\n",
    "    'axes.grid': True, 'grid.color': '#e8e8e8', 'axes.axisbelow': True,\n",
    "    'axes.titlesize': 11, 'axes.titleweight': 'bold', 'legend.frameon': False,\n",
    "})\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Likelihood for Poisson: MLE is x_bar ─────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# X1,...,Xn ~ Poisson(lambda): L(lambda) = prod exp(-lambda)*lambda^xi / xi!\n",
    "# log L(lambda) = -n*lambda + sum(xi)*log(lambda) + const\n",
    "# MLE: d/dlambda log L = 0 => lambda_hat = x_bar\n",
    "\n",
    "lambda_true = 3.0\n",
    "ns_demo     = [3, 10, 50]\n",
    "lambdas     = np.linspace(0.5, 7, 500)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(14, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax, n_demo in zip(axes, ns_demo):\n",
    "    data = np.random.poisson(lambda_true, n_demo)\n",
    "    log_lik = -n_demo * lambdas + data.sum() * np.log(lambdas)\n",
    "    mle     = data.mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.plot(lambdas, log_lik - log_lik.max(), color='#4361ee', lw=2.5)\n",
    "    ax.axvline(mle,         color='#f72585', lw=2, linestyle='--', label=f'MLE $\\\\hat{{\\\\lambda}}={mle:.2f}$')\n",
    "    ax.axvline(lambda_true, color='#06d6a0', lw=2, linestyle=':',  label=f'True $\\\\lambda={lambda_true}$')\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'Log-likelihood: Poisson, n={n_demo}\\nData: {data[:5]}{\"...\" if n_demo>5 else \"\"}')\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('$\\\\lambda$'); ax.set_ylabel('$\\\\ell(\\\\lambda) - \\\\ell(\\\\hat{\\\\lambda})$')\n",
    "    ax.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
    "    ax.set_ylim(-20, 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Likelihood function — MLE = $\\\\bar{X}$ for Poisson\\n'\n",
    "             'Wider curve = less information (small n); sharper = more information (large n)',\n",
    "             fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Invariance of the MLE\n",
    "\n",
    "If $\\hat{\\theta}$ is the MLE of $\\theta$, then $g(\\hat{\\theta})$ is the MLE of $g(\\theta)$ for any function $g$.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the **invariance principle** — one of the most useful properties of MLEs.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Example:** If $\\hat{\\lambda}$ is the MLE of $\\lambda$ for Poisson, then $e^{-\\hat{\\lambda}}$ is the MLE of $P(X=0) = e^{-\\lambda}$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Asymptotic properties of the MLE\n",
    "\n",
    "Under regularity conditions (Cramér conditions), as $n \\to \\infty$:\n",
    "\n",
    "**Consistency:** $\\hat{\\theta}_{\\text{MLE}} \\xrightarrow{p} \\theta_0$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Asymptotic normality:**\n",
    "$$\\sqrt{n}(\\hat{\\theta}_{\\text{MLE}} - \\theta_0) \\xrightarrow{d} \\mathcal{N}\\!\\left(0, [I(\\theta_0)]^{-1}\\right)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Asymptotic efficiency:** The MLE achieves the Cramér-Rao lower bound asymptotically — no consistent estimator can have a smaller asymptotic variance.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Observed Fisher information:**\n",
    "$$\\hat{I}_n = -\\frac{\\partial^2 \\ell}{\\partial \\theta^2}\\bigg|_{\\theta=\\hat\\theta}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The estimated asymptotic variance of the MLE is $\\widehat{\\text{Var}}(\\hat\\theta) = 1/\\hat{I}_n$, giving the standard error $\\widehat{\\text{SE}} = 1/\\sqrt{\\hat{I}_n}$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── MLE consistency and asymptotic normality for Gamma(alpha, beta) ───────\n",
    "from scipy.special import digamma, polygamma\n",
    "\n",
    "# Gamma(alpha, beta): MLE via method of moments as starting point, then numerical\n",
    "alpha_true, beta_true = 3.0, 2.0\n",
    "ns_test = [10, 30, 100, 500]\n",
    "n_reps  = 5000\n",
    "\n",
    "def gamma_mle(x):\n",
    "    \"\"\"MLE for Gamma(alpha, beta) using Newton-Raphson on score equation.\"\"\"\n",
    "    log_xbar = np.log(x.mean())\n",
    "    mean_logx = np.log(x).mean()\n",
    "    # MoM starting point\n",
    "    alpha0 = 0.5 / (log_xbar - mean_logx)\n",
    "    # Newton-Raphson\n",
    "    for _ in range(50):\n",
    "        alpha0 = alpha0 - (np.log(alpha0) - digamma(alpha0) - (log_xbar - mean_logx)) / \\\n",
    "                          (1/alpha0 - polygamma(1, alpha0))\n",
    "    beta0 = x.mean() / alpha0\n",
    "    return alpha0, beta0\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 4, figsize=(14, 7))\n",
    "x_norm = np.linspace(-4, 4, 300)\n",
    "\n",
    "for col, n_demo in enumerate(ns_test):\n",
    "    alpha_hats, beta_hats = [], []\n",
    "    for _ in range(n_reps):\n",
    "        x = np.random.gamma(alpha_true, beta_true, n_demo)\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            a, b = gamma_mle(x)\n",
    "            alpha_hats.append(a); beta_hats.append(b)\n",
    "        except:\n",
    "            pass\n",
    "    alpha_hats = np.array(alpha_hats)\n",
    "    beta_hats  = np.array(beta_hats)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Standardize alpha_hat\n",
    "    # Asymptotic SE from Fisher info of Gamma\n",
    "    I_alpha = polygamma(1, alpha_true) - 1/alpha_true  # approximate\n",
    "    se_alpha = 1 / np.sqrt(n_demo * I_alpha)\n",
    "    z_alpha = (alpha_hats - alpha_true) / se_alpha\n",
    "\n",
    "    for row, (vals, name, true_val, title) in enumerate([\n",
    "        (alpha_hats, '$\\\\hat{\\\\alpha}$', alpha_true, f'MLE $\\\\hat{{\\\\alpha}}$, n={n_demo}'),\n",
    "        (z_alpha,    'standardized', 0, f'Standardized, n={n_demo}'),\n",
    "    ]):\n",
    "        ax = axes[row, col]\n",
    "        ax.hist(vals, bins=50, density=True, color='#4361ee', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='white')\n",
    "        if row == 0:\n",
    "            ax.axvline(true_val, color='#f72585', lw=2, linestyle='--', label=f'True={true_val}')\n",
    "            ax.axvline(vals.mean(), color='#06d6a0', lw=1.5, label=f'Mean={vals.mean():.2f}')\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            ax.plot(x_norm, stats.norm.pdf(x_norm), 'r-', lw=2, label='N(0,1)')\n",
    "        ax.set_title(title, fontsize=9)\n",
    "        ax.legend(fontsize=7)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('MLE for Gamma: consistency (row 1) and asymptotic normality (row 2)',\n",
    "             fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Numerical MLE and profile likelihood\n",
    "\n",
    "When the score equation has no closed form, we maximize $\\ell(\\theta)$ numerically.\n",
    "\n",
    "For multiparameter models, the **profile likelihood** for a scalar component $\\theta_1$ is:\n",
    "$$\\ell_P(\\theta_1) = \\max_{\\theta_2} \\ell(\\theta_1, \\theta_2)$$\n",
    "This eliminates nuisance parameters and is used to construct confidence intervals (notebook 07)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Numerical MLE for mixture model ──────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Observe data from 0.7*N(0,1) + 0.3*N(mu2, 1), estimate mu2\n",
    "\n",
    "mu2_true = 4.0\n",
    "n_data   = 300\n",
    "labels   = np.random.binomial(1, 0.3, n_data)\n",
    "data     = np.where(labels, np.random.normal(mu2_true, 1, n_data),\n",
    "                             np.random.normal(0, 1, n_data))\n",
    "\n",
    "def neg_log_lik(mu2):\n",
    "    lik = 0.7 * stats.norm.pdf(data, 0, 1) + 0.3 * stats.norm.pdf(data, mu2, 1)\n",
    "    return -np.sum(np.log(np.maximum(lik, 1e-300)))\n",
    "\n",
    "mu2_grid = np.linspace(1, 7, 300)\n",
    "log_liks = [-neg_log_lik(m) for m in mu2_grid]\n",
    "\n",
    "result   = optimize.minimize_scalar(neg_log_lik, bounds=(1, 7), method='bounded')\n",
    "mu2_hat  = result.x\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 4))\n",
    "ax.plot(mu2_grid, np.array(log_liks) - max(log_liks), color='#4361ee', lw=2.5)\n",
    "ax.axvline(mu2_hat,  color='#f72585', lw=2, linestyle='--', label=f'MLE $\\\\hat{{\\\\mu}}_2 = {mu2_hat:.2f}$')\n",
    "ax.axvline(mu2_true, color='#06d6a0', lw=2, linestyle=':',  label=f'True $\\\\mu_2 = {mu2_true}$')\n",
    "ax.axhline(-1.92, color='gray', lw=1.5, linestyle=':', label='95% CI cutoff ($-\\\\chi^2_{0.95}/2$)')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('$\\\\mu_2$'); ax.set_ylabel('$\\\\ell(\\\\mu_2) - \\\\ell(\\\\hat{\\\\mu}_2)$')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Profile log-likelihood for $\\\\mu_2$ in Gaussian mixture\\n'\n",
    "             '95% CI = values where profile log-lik > -1.92')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Key takeaways\n",
    "\n",
    "| Property | Statement |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| MLE definition | $\\hat\\theta = \\arg\\max_\\theta \\ell(\\theta)$ |\n",
    "| Invariance | $g(\\hat\\theta)$ is MLE of $g(\\theta)$ |\n",
    "| Consistency | $\\hat\\theta \\xrightarrow{p} \\theta_0$ |\n",
    "| Asymptotic normality | $\\sqrt{n}(\\hat\\theta - \\theta_0) \\xrightarrow{d} \\mathcal{N}(0, I(\\theta_0)^{-1})$ |\n",
    "| Asymptotic efficiency | Achieves the Cramér-Rao bound in the limit |\n",
    "| Observed information | $\\hat{I}_n = -\\ell''(\\hat\\theta)$ gives estimated SE |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Next:** notebook 07 — interval estimation: using the MLE and its asymptotic distribution to construct confidence intervals."
   ]
  }
 ],
